result.execSummary:
The defendant Daniel O Jeffers was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Daniel O Jeffers is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Daniel O Jeffers was found guilty of OWI Cause Injury (2+), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(2)(a)1.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Decision and Order Denying Motion for Sentence Modification signed and filed.  Notice to parties.  alp
Per Order of the Presiding Judge, Felony Division, this motion/request is hereby assigned to the Hon. William S. Pocan, Br. 26, for review. mag
DENFENDANTS MOTION FOR POST-CONVICTION MODIFICATION OF SENTENCE

Defendant Daniel O Jeffers in court with attorney David G. Kingstad.  Lucy Kronforst appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  COUNT 1:    
Statements by each counsel and defendant as to sentencing.  
  Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.  Court ordered restitution in the amount of $919.91 owed to the City of Milwaukee Department of Waterworks and $512.00 owed to Maxwell C., payable as a condition of probation.  If not paid, a civil judgment to be entered.

Court sentenced defendant to pay a FINE of $1,800.00  PLUS all costs, penalties and surcharges, including the mandatory DNA surcharge, as a condition of probation  or, as a penalty if not paid, a civil judgment to be entered.

Court ordered Intoxicated Driver Assessment; form filed; copy to defendant.
Court ordered defendant's driving privileges revoked for 24 months.
Court ordered ignitition interlock for 12 months, consecutive to revocation.
 
The Court sentenced the defendant to a TOTAL LENGTH of imprisonment of 4 years, consecutive to any other sentence.
The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons is 2 years with credit for 0 days
time served.
The Court orders the defendant to serve a maximum term of EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 2 years.

The court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 3
years with the following conditions:
*Serve condition time of 6 months in the HOC, Huber privileges for work and treatment.  Court recommends release to the Day Reporting Center and electronic monitoring.
*Alcohol and drug assessment and comply with any treatment deemed necessary by the department.
*Random urine screens.  No positive results.
*Maintain absolute sobriety.
*No illegal drugs.
*No controlled substances without valid prescription.
*No contact with drug community.
*Seek and maintain full time employment.
*Cognitive Behavior Therapy.
